-demo.mmDemo-actors.OTuQvpGudSH4Fxg1]{Conjuror Crew [13-14]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.ZSbantD5tiFPVLed]{Conjuror Crew [15-16]}</p></div></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\"><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Cultist Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Cutpurse Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Doctor Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Enforcer Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\"><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Guard Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Guardian Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Hunter Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Hydromancer Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\"><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Mage For Hire Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Monk Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Necromancer Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Ogre Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\"><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Priestess Crews by level</strong></summary><div style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:1.0em\"><p></p></div></details></td><td class=\"crews\"><details open style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Provocateur Crews by level</strong></summary><div style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:1.0em\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.NFHzNYHn9zR8xpsO]{Provocateur Troupe, Ragtag [3-4]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.IkKqzHuP6xfxo8tx]{Provocateur Troupe [5-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.jN3Dj5lbMWyr8V4O]{Provocateur Troupe [7-8]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.aYTgRnmzyaAgDEZX]{Provocateur Troupe [9-10]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.2MItLiBB4U6zuTrH]{Provocateur Troupe [11-12]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.JBtBitMPSWsFKzLC]{Provocateur Troupe [13-14]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.G7oAfCK1t0iRBxb1]{Provocateur Troupe [15-16]}</p></div></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Ravager Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Runic Warrior Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\"><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Sprite Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Tactician Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Wrestler Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><strong> </strong></td></tr></tbody></table><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Usage</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>NPCs crews are intended to be direct replacements for individual NPCs of the same level, with minimal impact on balance. Thus, instead of introducing a new NPC mook of 12th level as your players fight their way through an organization, you might instead introduce a Crew made up of 8th level NPCs that the players have fought before. By utilizing Crews in this fashion, it will feel like their foes are forced to throw more enemies at them as they grow in power. More details about the design philosophy of Crews and their usage can be found in the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.9gfeVJcuMhGzcjlY]{Crew Templates} entry. </p><p>The Crews presented above are all pre-modified using the Crew Template, however as is typical for the Crew Template, their equipment has not been adjusted. In a campaign where you are making extensive use of Crews you will want to reward the party with loot from other sources, for example, story rewards or loot from bosses.  While you can add additional copies of each item carried by the Crew to more accurately represent all the arms and armour carried by the crew, doing so results in the party receiving a lot of low level gear that is, in my experience, not worth tracking.</p><p>As is typical for the NPCs presented in Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1, Crews are presented with the bare minimum for gear, based on table 2-4: Safe Items from the Gamemastery Guide, focusing solely on fundamental rune progression. When adapting these Crews for use in your games as adversaries, you may wish to equip your Crews with additional consumables that are narratively appropriate. </p></div></details></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"J5arLCsj7pbrI1eQ","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Descriptive Templates","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">NPCs with Personality</h4><hr /><p style=\"width:85%\">Here you'll find a collection of templates that allow you to modify your NPCs based on a descriptive adjective. A handle of templates have been selected for the Demo, with the remainder being found only in the full version of the module. Each template will give the base creature a unique ability or action that is evocative of the templates' adjective. Many of these templates will also increase or decrease the level of the creature.</p><h2 class=\"stylish\">Instructions</h2><div style=\"width:90%;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:3.5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><h3 class=\"dark\">Step 1. Select Template</h3><p style=\"padding-bottom:0;margin-bottom:0\">Select a Descriptive Template from those listed below that matches the evocative quirk or characteristic you want your NPC to have. The Templates are organized by level adjustment, with +1 templates increasing the level of the creature they are applied to by 1, while -1 templates decrease the level of the creature they are applied to by 1.</p></div><table style=\"width:85.1095%;border-style:hidden;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:41.3379%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;height:19px\"><strong>Level Adjustment</strong></td><td style=\"width:58.8336%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;height:19px\"><strong>Templates</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:50px\"><td style=\"width:41.3379%;text-align:center;color:#050e18;background:#CFC5AF\"><strong>+1</strong></td><td style=\"width:58.8336%;text-align:center;background:#CFC5AF;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-templates.J3mK8pMKdEsJ1xgL]{Bold Template}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Cunning Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Hardy Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Lucky Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Protective Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Sorcerous Template</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:41.3379%;text-align:center;background:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><strong>0</strong></td><td style=\"width:58.8336%;text-align:center;background:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-templates.Mv8TaQXZeg3IfQi9]{Boastful Template}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Brutish Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Cowardly Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Oblivious Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Slight Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Watchful Template</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:41.3379%;text-align:center;color:#050e18;background:#CFC5AF\"><strong>-1</strong></td><td style=\"width:58.8336%;text-align:center;background:#CFC5AF;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Clumsy Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-templates.lCM1lqs9zB1PWHPn]{Foolish Template}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Frail Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Punchable Template</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:41.3379%;text-align:center;color:#050e18;background:#e3ddcf\"><strong>-2</strong></td><td style=\"width:58.8336%;text-align:center;background:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Convalescent Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Feeble Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Inept Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Unlucky Template</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:41.3379%;text-align:center;color:#050e18;background:#CFC5AF\"><strong>-3</strong></td><td style=\"width:58.8336%;text-align:center;background:#CFC5AF;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Doddering Template</p></td></tr></tbody></table><div style=\"width:90%;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:3.5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><h3 class=\"dark\">Step 2. Apply Template</h3><p>Apply your selected Descriptive Template from Step 1 by dragging it to the NPC token or character sheet, of your choice. After you have dropped it on the token or sheet the Template will automatically apply any appropriate bonuses or penalties and grant any new abilities using the grant item rule element to the NPC. </p><h3 class=\"dark\">Step 3. Manual Adjustments</h3><p>Many of the Descriptive Templates will require small adjustments that could not be automated. If the NPC's maximum HP has increased after the application of the template, you will need to adjust their current HP to match their new maximum. If your base creature has non-strike effects or abilities that deal damage, the damage of these abilities will need to be manually adjusted according to the instructions on each template. This is also an opportune time to review your chosen template for other required manual adjustments. If you have selected one of the level -2 templates you may need to adjust the creature's spellcasting entries. </p><p>Additionally, while you're reviewing your template, take note of any effects listed under the \"effect\" heading on the template, as these will need to be manually adjudicated during play.</p></div><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Usage</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>These templates are designed to allow you to quickly adjust individual creatures to have particular evocative quirks, some of which may be positive and others detrimental. In either case, the creature's level will be adjusted as described in the Level Adjustment column of the table.</p><p>While these templates might create a creature that would typically be considered uncommon or even rare, I recommend that you do not increase the DC to recall knowledge. The strengths and weaknesses of the various templates are key pieces of information to share with your players and have been designed with the expectation that your players will be targeting these weaknesses or attempting to avoid their opposition's strengths. Making that information easier for your players to learn will make for more satisfying and memorable encounters with the modified NPCs, by allowing players to plan around their abilities. </p></div></details><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Design Philosophy</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>The templates were designed to focus on active abilities, and specific strengths or weaknesses the players can defend against or exploit. Most templates are associated with an ability that the creature either, can use, in the case of beneficial abilities, or must use in response to a certain trigger, in the case of detrimental abilities.</p><p>Level Plus templates have been designed to be slightly weaker than an elite creature on average, but will out perform a standard Elite creature, when doing something a creature that could be described with that adjective could reasonably expected to excel at.</p><p>Level +0 templates have been designed to include some positives and negatives and produce creatures that should have roughly the same capabilities as the bae creature, but will be slightly easier to combat for a party that successfully recalls knowledge about these creatures, and slightly harder for those that do not.</p><p>Level Minus templates have been designed to be slightly stronger than a weak creature on average with key detriments and mandatory free actions that the players can exploit to make these creatures easier to handle.</p></div></details></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"ri8fswkWP7Bimh8l","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Generic Spellcasters","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">Generic Spellcasters</h4><hr /><p style=\"width:85%\">The full version of Mercenary Marketplace contains a catalogue of prebuilt NPCs spellcasters presented without spell lists. These NPCs are intended to be used alongside the @Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.dLMmYYevbHCikFnH]{Generate a Random Spell List} macro to quickly create unique casters for your world.</p><p style=\"width:85%\">In volume 1, each spellcasting Tradition is represented by a single NPC which has been built to be usable as a creature from any level between 1 and 20. </p></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"XAdP7FZyWoeMEfRI","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Introduction to Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div style=\"width:100%;margin:0 auto;padding-top:1rem;padding-bottom:1rem\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div style=\"width:100%;margin:0 auto;padding:1% 2.5%\"><div style=\"justify-content:space-between;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap\"><div style=\"flex:1;background-color:#d9d1bf;padding-left:1.5em;padding-right:1.5em;border:10px solid #CFC5AF\"><h2 class=\"plain\">Introduction</h2><hr /><p>Thank you for picking up the Demo of Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1. Within this module you'll find a curated selection of content from Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1. The full version contains 373 new generic NPCs ready to use in your campaigns and 29 templates that will let you customize your existing library of creatures. </p><p>Quick links to help you find all your new content are provided in the directory. For quick access to the directory, save the @Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.X1a1jfoWS4EqGETN]{Toggle MM Volume 1 Directory} macro to your hotbar.</p><p>If you encounter any bugs or other issues, you can report them at the associated <a class=\"href\" href=\"https://github.com/velara/MercenaryMarketplaceVolume1/issues\">GitHub Issues Tracker</a></p><p>I hope you have as much fun using all these new NPCs as I did creating them!</p><h2 class=\"plain\">New NPCs</h2><hr /><p>There are five broad categories of NPCs included in Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.JWFJTzMI86q256tm]{NPCs with Classes} which are designed to be iconic representatives of the various classes from the Core Rulebook.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.m3ez8MLOFi0NWUSH]{NPCs with Jobs} which are designed to excel at performing specific roles in combat.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.XAdP7FZyWoeMEfRI]{Generic Spellcasters} which are fully statted-out NPCs awaiting the addition of your custom, or randomly generated, spell list.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.J5arLCsj7pbrI1eQ]{Crews} which are small groups of foes to challenge your players with. The provided Crews are examples of NPCs that have had the Crew template applied to them.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.LVylAkC1NWnXxLul]{Troops} which are large groups of foes to challenge your players with.</p><p>You can find all the new NPCs included in Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1 one of three ways.</p><ol><li><p style=\"font-weight:normal;color:black\">By browsing the NPC Catalogues listed in the Directory. For ease of browsing, the new NPCs have been curated into five organized catalogues based on type. Each catalogue is sorted by level and class or combat role as appropriate.</p></li><li><p style=\"font-weight:normal;color:black\">Using the Bestiary Browser. You can browse your new NPCs using the Source filter. Additionally, NPCs have been given tags based on either their class or combat role, allowing you to filter by those traits.</p></li><li><p style=\"font-weight:normal;color:black\">Opening the Mercenary Marketplace Vol. 1 NPCs Compendium in your Compendium Packs tab.</p></li></ol><h2 class=\"plain\">New Templates</h2><hr /><p>There are three types of templates included in Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.QibnMkhhPYrIrwG5]{Ancestry Templates} which allow you to quickly apply an ancestry to an existing NPC.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.9gfeVJcuMhGzcjlY]{Crew Templates} which allow you to convert any NPC into a crew of four to six NPCs working in unison.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.ri8fswkWP7Bimh8l]{Descriptive Templates} which grant an NPC specific thematic advantages or detriments based on a descriptive adjective.</p><p>You can find all your new Templates in one of three ways.</p><ol><li><p style=\"font-weight:normal;color:black\">By browsing the Template Catalogues listed in the Directory. For ease of browsing, the templates have been curated into three organized catalogues by template type.</p></li><li><p style=\"font-weight:normal;color:black\">Using the Compendium Browser. You can browse your new Templates by using the trait filter for the Template trait.</p></li><li><p style=\"font-weight:normal;color:black\">Opening the Mercenary Marketplace Vol. 1 Creature Templates Compendium in your Compendium Packs tab.</p></li></ol><h2 class=\"plain\">Other Content</h2><hr /><p>With the addition of Crews and Templates a couple new traits have been introduced that have some associated rules. These rules have been detailed in the appropriate sections, but for ease of reference have been complied in the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.ysvcY0zFgA6pn1Ak]{New Rules} journal entry.</p><p>This module also includes some new @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.62pBbzbgeMFzOeHD]{Macros}, the first of which generates randomized spell lists based on user input, and is ideal for use with the generic spellcasters. The second can be used to quickly set up the requisite spellcasting entries for the Sorcerous NPC template, which allows you to quickly add a splash of magical power to your NPCs. </p><h2 class=\"plain\">Full Version</h2><hr /><p>If you end up loving the content of the Mercenary Marketplace Demo, then please consider supporting my work by purchasing the <a href=\"https://velara.itch.io/mercenary-marketplace-v1\">full version</a>.</p></div><div style=\"flex:0 0 1em\"><h4> </h4></div><div id=\"directory\" style=\"flex:0 1 16em;background-color:#0d253f;padding-left:1em;padding-right:1em;padding-top:1em;border:10px solid #050e18\"><div style=\"position:sticky;top:5%;width:16em\"><img style=\"border:0;margin-top:-0.3em\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/directory.png\" /><h4 class=\"directory\">NPC Catalogues</h4><hr /><div style=\"margin-left:3em;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.JWFJTzMI86q256tm]{NPCs with Classes}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.m3ez8MLOFi0NWUSH]{NPCs with Jobs}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.XAdP7FZyWoeMEfRI]{Generic Spellcasters}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.J5arLCsj7pbrI1eQ]{Crews}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.LVylAkC1NWnXxLul]{Troops}</p></div><h4 class=\"directory\">Template Catalogues</h4><hr /><div style=\"margin-left:3em;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.QibnMkhhPYrIrwG5]{Ancestry Templates}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.9gfeVJcuMhGzcjlY]{Crew Templates}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.ri8fswkWP7Bimh8l]{Descriptive Templates}</p></div><h4 class=\"directory\">Other Links</h4><hr /><div style=\"margin-left:3em;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.ysvcY0zFgA6pn1Ak]{New Rules}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.62pBbzbgeMFzOeHD]{Macros}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.2h7OGxE2sIBY8h2k]{Credits &amp; License}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\"><a style=\"color:floralwhite\" href=\"https://github.com/velara/MercenaryMarketVolume1/issues\">GitHub Issues Tracker</a></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\"><a style=\"color:floralwhite\" href=\"https://github.com/velara/MercenaryMarketplaceVolume1/releases\">Release Notes</a></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\"><a style=\"color:floralwhite\" href=\"https://www.patreon.com/MercenaryMarketplace\">Patreon</a></p></div></div></div></div><p style=\"color:floralwhite;font-size:0.8em;margin-left:0.5em\">Compatibility with Pathfinder Second Edition requires Pathfinder Second Edition from Paizo Inc. See <a style=\"color:floralwhite\" href=\"http://localhost:30000/paizo.com/pathfinder\">paizo.com/pathfinder</a> to learn more about Pathfinder. Paizo Inc. does not guarantee compatibility, and does not endorse this product.</p></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"gkN2qUJTnou7N3nS","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Macros","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">Macros</h4><hr /><div style=\"margin-left:10%;width:90%\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;margin-left:-5%\">There are eight macros included in Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1. Seven of which are available in the demo.</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.X1a1jfoWS4EqGETN]{Toggle Mercenary Marketplace Vol. 1 Directory Macro}.</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.dLMmYYevbHCikFnH]{Generate a Random Spell List Macro}.<br />@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.GFc0qSPQQb7UrN06]{Arcane Ancestral Cantrip}.<br />@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.6h2oa86ZN4xOPSQq]{Divine Ancestral Cantrip}.<br />@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.t73Cb6tJzvKwd3sI]{Occult Ancestral Cantrip}.<br />@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.g5wjnIPgSqByo7Kq]{Primal Ancestral Cantrips}.<br />@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.A36zBYLenNrDZdc6]{Grant Innate Spells}.</p></div><h2 class=\"stylish\" style=\"margin-top:1.5em\">Toggle Mercenary Marketplace Directory</h2><p style=\"width:90%;margin:0;padding:0;margin-left:5%\">When run, this macro will either:</p><div style=\"width:90%;margin-left:10%\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\"><strong>A)</strong> Open the Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1 Directory journal entry.</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\"><strong>B)</strong> If the Directory is already open and not your active window, it will bring it to the front and maximize it.</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\"><strong>C)</strong> If the Directory is your active window it will close it.</p></div><h2 class=\"stylish\" style=\"margin-top:1em\">Generate a Random Spell List - (Limited in Demo)</h2><p style=\"width:90%\">When run, this macro will generate a random list of spells of your chosen tradition based on your specifications. You can limit the rarity of spells it can pull from, select specific schools you'd like to prioritize for inclusion, include heightened versions of spells on the list, and prioritize or ban specific traits.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">The macro will generate a number of spells for each level based on the value you input, with no duplicates. If no spells remain that match your specifications, it will instead pull from an unfiltered list.</p><p>The demo version is limited to generating lists containing only cantrips and level 1 spells.</p><h2 class=\"stylish\">Sorcerous Template Setup - (Full Version Only)</h2><p style=\"width:90%\">When run, this macro will add sorcerous spellcasting to either the NPC character sheet you have open (if it is your active window), or the NPC token you have selected if no NPC character sheet is your currently active window.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">It will add a spontaneous spellcasting entry with 1 spell slot per level, and a focus spellcasting entry with 1 focus point and populate these entries with the granted spells and bloodlines spells for your selected Sorcerous bloodline. The macro will also set the NPC's skill for the skill associated with that bloodline's spellcasting tradition to a value determined by the NPC's level, if that value is higher than the NPC's unmodified skill.</p><h2 class=\"stylish\">Grant Ancestral Cantrips</h2><p style=\"width:90%\">When run, these macro will add an innate spellcasting entry of the appropriate tradition (arcane, divine, occult, or primal) to either the NPC character sheet you have open (if it is your active window), or the NPC token you have selected if no NPC character sheet is your currently active window.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">Each tradition has a separate macro, which will prompt you to select a single cantrip of that tradition, it will then add a innate spellcasting entry of the appropriate tradition and populate the spellcasting entry with your chosen cantrip and set the spell DC and spell attack modifier to appropriate values. <br /></p><p style=\"width:90%\"><strong>Note </strong>if the NPC already has a spellcasting entry you will likely wish to modify the added DC to better reflect their spellcasting proficiency. There is a separate macro for each</p><h2 class=\"stylish\">Grant Innate Spells</h2><p style=\"width:90%\">When run, this macro will add an innate spellcasting entry to either the NPC character sheet you have open (if it is your active window), or the NPC token you have selected if no NPC character sheet is your currently active window.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">The entries tradition and key stat are set by flags on the actor. Similar flags also allow you to specify the spells to be added to this entry. Using these flags it will add an innate spellcasting entry of the appropriate tradition and populate the spellcasting entry with the spell specified in the flags heightened to the specified level and with the specified number of uses.</p><p style=\"width:90%\"></p><p style=\"width:90%\"><strong>Technical Specifications</strong><br />For an example see the rule elements for @Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-abilities.G2DiKLuUrOQ8ifUN]{Elf, Seer}.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">The path to store the flags should you wish to make your own is: flags.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace.grantedSpellcasting.{tradition}. Where {tradition} is replaced with the desired tradition arcane, divine, occult, or primal.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">The key ability modifier is stored at mercenary-marketplace.grantedSpellcasting.{tradition}.keyStat and should be specified using the three letter abbreviation str, dex, con, int, wis, or cha.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">The spell are stored at mercenary-marketplace.grantedSpellcasting.{tradition}.spells. Each spell is added in the following format. [\"Source\", \"Spell Name\", Level, Uses]. Level and Uses can be omitted in which case they will default to the spells base level and 1 respectively. The spell name should be capitalized for example \"Detect Magic\", and the source entry can be set to any string value.</p><p></p></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"62pBbzbgeMFzOeHD","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"New Rules","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">New Rules - Quick Reference</h4><hr /><h2 class=\"stylish\">Crew Trait</h2><p style=\"width:90%\">The Crew trait indicates that a creature is actually a collection of 4 to 6 trained individuals working together in unison. Any creature with the Crew trait is treated as a single creature for the purposes of spells and effects. However, it may be selected twice for abilities that require you to select two adjacent creatures, such as swipe.</p><h2 class=\"stylish\">Mandatory Trait</h2><p style=\"width:90%\">The Mandatory trait is only ever applied to abilities with a trigger. If the trigger occurs for an ability with the Mandatory trait a creature with that ability must use it, even if it is to the creature's detriment.</p></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"ysvcY0zFgA6pn1Ak","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"NPCs with Classes","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">NPCs with Class</h4><hr /><p style=\"width:92%\">In this Demo only the Cleric, Fighter, Rogue and Wizard are available. All other detail dropdowns are empty.</p><p style=\"width:92%\">Here you'll find a catalogue of NPCs built to resemble members of one of the twelve classes from the Core Rulebook.  In Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1, each class is represented by a single NPC, with multiple scaled iterations allowing for NPCs from level  1 and 18. </p><h2 class=\"plain\">Catalogue of NPCs by Class</h2><hr /><table style=\"margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;width:92%;border-style:hidden\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;height:19px;font-size:0.9em\"><strong>Alchemist</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;height:19px;font-size:0.9em\"><strong>Barbarian</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;height:19px;font-size:0.9em\"><strong>Bard</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px;vertical-align:top\"><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Alchemists by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Barbarians by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Bards by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Champion</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Cleric</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Druid</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px;vertical-align:top\"><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Champions by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Clerics by level</strong></summary><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.uRLvqoIAtjGzWCFZ]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [1-2]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.XV93IR6dQqdhJ9To]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [3-4]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.GucfeJ75iqQQGqCa]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [5-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.JS3iVWBmEJ9hcl7m]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [7-8]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.vvbH0YtUmqWPlELs]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [9-10]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.N7Dg9H5qQzYgn4PO]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [11-12]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.ajgMdZpsbHSuPRfT]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [13-14]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.6VUxvixmcqOFgFUe]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [15-16]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.tnNUGJ9PD6BmtRdO]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [17-18]}</p></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Druids by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Fighter</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Monk</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Ranger</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px;vertical-align:top\"><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Fighters by level</strong></summary><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.gEP3r7Idh2pxEZdc]{Mercenary Fighter [1-3]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.20jaZjNJ5jMGntNf]{Mercenary Fighter [4-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.MXs60Y75oSTE0z56]{Mercenary Fighter [7-9]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.hctTM0VU9jOX1ek4]{Mercenary Fighter [10-12]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.VKm7k5if12mVLYv5]{Mercenary Fighter [13-15]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.meHZBMGNlgw3Gbz5]{Mercenary Fighter [16-18]}</p></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Monks by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Rangers by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Rogue</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Sorcerer</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Wizard</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px;vertical-align:top\"><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Rogues by level</strong></summary><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.tJa8LcWzbJxYcDst]{Mercenary Rogue [1-3]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.QkC0uFzNYGqS97mM]{Mercenary Rogue [4-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.JHUiDYDunNrR6fQZ]{Mercenary Rogue [7-9]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.H9bUMe2wOA08wIok]{Mercenary Rogue [10-12]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.521euvbF9z0ChdGI]{Mercenary Rogue [13-15]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.0FUWn1DRgjBuiDHQ]{Mercenary Rogue [16-18]}</p></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Sorcerers by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Wizards by level</strong></summary><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.39WcoXLAVE19JUEa]{Mercenary Wizard [1-2]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.NwJxTzZb7XwmbGRF]{Mercenary Wizard [3-4]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.WkED36XGaWaLVB8s]{Mercenary Wizard [5-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.uRBF4jYThQUI6YN7]{Mercenary Wizard [7-8]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.Ela24uWRAQKJirxm]{Mercenary Wizard [9-10]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.gZhtAmEnlqLC7U8l]{Mercenary Wizard [11-12]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.5AvTCzq7towZNe61]{Mercenary Wizard [13-14]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.iS0JaR9u47qsFKL3]{Mercenary Wizard [15-16]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.R4kFk0cHffbdGhbw]{Mercenary Wizard [17-18]}</p></details></td></tr></tbody></table><div style=\"width:94%;margin:0 auto\"><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Usage</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>NPCs with class have been provided for use for levels between 1 and 18, allowing you to use them with minimal modification for the majority of any campaign.</p><p>Melee characters are listed with a range of three levels, for example [1-3]. The NPC is of the median level; however by applying either the Elite or Weak template, you can use those NPCs for the higher or lower level listed in the range. </p><p>Spellcasting characters are listed with a range of two levels, for example [1-2]. You'll find the actual NPC is the higher of the two levels. Given the increase in power and versatility that comes with learning a new level of spells, it is recommended that you do not use these NPCs with the Elite template, but they are readily compatible with the Weak template. Furthermore, given the adjustments applied by the Weak template to spell damage, I do not recommend adjusting the number of spell slots.</p><p>NPCs have been provided with a minimal amount of gear based on table 2-4: Safe Items from the Gamemastery Guide, focusing entirely on fundamental rune progression. While this means you can slot them into your game with a minimal impact on your party's treasure, if you are using them as the base for a significant foe you will want to expand upon and upgrade upon the gear provided, particularly in terms of consumables, worn or held magic items, and things like scrolls, staves and wands for spellcasting NPCs. Please note however, the NPC statistics already reflect appropriate values for creatures of their level, based on Paizo's creature creation guidelines, so if you are upgrading the fundamental runes (+x potency runes, resilience, striking) I would recommend exercising caution with changing those values, although applying the effects of property runes should be acceptable, especially if your players are level 5+. </p><p>These NPCs are designed to be most appropriate for use as named antagonists,  either directly unmodified or tweaked to match your needs. While NPCs with Class can be dropped into the world to represent generic antagonists of the appropriate player class, care should be taken to avoid the Skyrim bandit problem, where all the background NPCs level up with the party. If you are looking to challenge a high level party with generic underlings, either @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.J5arLCsj7pbrI1eQ]{Crews} or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.LVylAkC1NWnXxLul]{Troops} may be more suitable while maintaining a stronger sense of progression. </p></div></details><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Design Philosophy</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>These NPCs have been designed to emulate player classes, although in many cases abilities have been simplified, condensed or reflavoured to make the NPCs easier to run for GMs. To appropriately capture the flavour of their respective classes, these NPCs with Class tend to have more abilities, than the other NPCs included in Mercenary Market Volume 1, making them more complex to run. These design choices make NPCs with class most appropriate for use as named antagonists. Although, these NPCs will still tend to have fewer  abilities than a PC of the same level, and no attempt has been made to include skill feats or ancestry feats, instead trading that versatility for the slight increase in raw power that is intrinsic to Paizo's creature building guidelines.</p><p>While we have attempted to capture the essence and flavour of each class, we have not restricted ourselves to the abilities and feats described in the core rulebook, some custom abilities have been created. While these new abilities have not been written up as player facing feats, they could be adapted for uncommon or rare player options. Although, if adapted without any tweaking, they will tend to be slightly more powerful than standard player options of the same level, as NPCs tend have fewer, slightly more powerful abilities, to make up for their lack of versatility and to make them easier to run.</p><p>Generally an attempt has been made to remove or modify abilities that are likely to be frustrating for players. For example, many classes get abilities to upgrade successes on saves to critical successes for their highest save, which given the relatively high saves of NPCs can be very frustrating for spellcasting PCs. To counteract this, we have omitted many of these abilities, except in cases were we felt these abilities were essential to the flavour of the class, such as Evasion on the Rogue.</p><p>The progression of these characters is modelled after that of their respective classes, with slight deviations as appropriate.</p></div></details></div></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"JWFJTzMI86q256tm","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"NPCs with Jobs","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">NPCs with Jobs</h4><hr /><p style=\"width:85%\">Here you'll find a catalogue of NPCs built to fill a particular combat role or job.  In volume 1, each role is represented by several NPCs. Multiple versions of different levels exist for each NPC. </p><p style=\"width:85%\">In this demo only the Doctor, Guardian and Necromancer are available, all the other detail dropdowns are empty.</p><h2 class=\"plain\">Catalogue of NPCs by Combat Role</h2><hr /><table style=\"margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;width:90%;border-style:hidden\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Artillery</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Bruiser</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Defender</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px;vertical-align:top\"><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Archers by level</strong></summary></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Hydromancers by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Enforcers by level</strong></summary></details><details styl