 and are not Open Game Content: All trademarks, registered trademarks, proper nouns (characters, deities, locations, etc., as well as all adjectives, names, titles, and descriptive terms derived from proper nouns), artworks, characters, dialogue, locations, organizations, plots, storylines, and trade dress. (Elements that have previously been designated as Open Game Content, or are exclusively derived from previous Open Game Content, or that are in the public domain are not included in this declaration.)</p><p><strong>Open Game Content:</strong> Except for material designated as Product Identity or External Tools (see above), the game mechanics of this Paizo game product are Open Game Content, as defined in the Open Game License version 1.0a, Section 1(d). No portion of this work other than the material designated as Open Game Content may be reproduced in any form without written permission.</p><p>Georgia and Sylfaen fonts are used under the terms of the <a class=\"href\" href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/fonts/font-faq\">Microsoft font redistribution license</a></p><p>Golden Art Deco borders used in the Mercenary Marketplace logo were designed by tartila / Freepik and are used under <a class=\"href\" href=\"http://www.freepik.com/terms_of_use\">license.</a></p><p>The Wall Blue Grunge Ancient Pattern used in the Mercenary Marketplace logo and Directory image was taken by djedj and use used under the <a class=\"href\" href=\"https://pixabay.com/service/license/\">Pixabay License.</a></p><p>The Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1 Cover Image is licensed under the <a class=\"href\" href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported License</a> and uses art from <a class=\"href\" href=\"https://www.deviantart.com/tomprante\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Tom Prante</a></p></div></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"2h7OGxE2sIBY8h2k","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":2700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Crew Templates","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">Crew Templates</h4><hr /><p style=\"width:90%\">The full version of Mercenary Marketplace contains crew templates which can be used to automatically turn any NPC in your collection into a Crew of 4 to 6 individuals working in unison.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">These templates will grant the Crew trait. Any creature with the Crew trait is treated as a single creature for the purposes of spells and effects. However, it may be selected twice for abilities that require you to select two adjacent creatures, such as swipe.</p><p>Below you will find a description of how to use the templates in the full of the module.</p><h2 class=\"stylish\">Instructions</h2><div style=\"width:90%;margin:0 auto\"><h3 class=\"dark\">Step 1. Select Template</h3><p>Select a Crew Template. There are two Crew Templates provided.</p><p>The <strong>Ragtag Crew Template</strong> which produces a Crew with a level 2-higher than that of the base creature.</p><p>The <strong>Crew Template</strong> which produces a Crew with a level 4-higher than that of the base creature.</p><h3 class=\"dark\">Step 2. Select Abilities</h3><p>Select Crew Abilities from the table below for your Crew. Select 1 ability if you are creating a Ragtag Crew or 2 if you are creating a standard Crew.</p><p>These abilities represent special training or capabilities the Crew has developed as a group. The abilities have been divided into Universal Abilities that are useful to all Crews, and Spellcaster Exclusive Abilities that are only useful if the base creature is a spellcaster. Please note that Simultaneous Casting and United Casting are mutually exclusive abilities.</p><table style=\"width:100%;border-style:hidden\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:100%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;height:19px\"><strong>Universal Abilities</strong></td></tr></tbody></table><table style=\"width:100%;border-style:hidden\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width:50%;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Back to Back</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Bodyguard Training</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Collateral Damage</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Collective Reflexes</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Concentrated Assault</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Diversified Strikes</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Formation Training</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Frontline Protection</strong></p></td><td style=\"width:50%;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Guarded Retreat</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Harrying Vanguard</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Perceptive Crew</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Reactive Punishment</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Scattered Shots</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Shared Defence</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Skilled Teamwork</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Team Flanking</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><table style=\"width:100%;border-style:hidden\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:100%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;height:19px\"><strong>Spellcaster Exclusive Abilities</strong></td></tr></tbody></table><table style=\"width:100%;border-style:hidden\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width:50%;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Collaborative Sustain</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Joint Summoning</strong></p></td><td style=\"width:50%;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>Simultaneous Casting</strong></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;text-align:start\"><strong>United Casting</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><h3 class=\"dark\">Step 3. Apply Template</h3><p>Apply your selected Crew Template from Step 1 by dragging it to the NPC token or character sheet of your choice. After you have dropped it on the token or sheet, you will need to answer a prompt asking you the size of the base creature you have applied the template to. Once you have input the base creature's size, subsequent prompts will pop up asking which abilities you would like to add to your new Crew. Each prompt will present a dropdown of all of the Crew Abilities listed above, in alphabetical order. After you have made your selection(s) the template will automatically adjust the base creature's statistics, and use the grant item rule element to automatically add your selected crew abilities to the base creature.</p><h3 class=\"dark\">Step 4. Manual Adjustments</h3><p>After applying your Crew Template and selecting your Crew Ability(s), there are a few manual changes you may need to make. Firstly, you will want to update the Crew's current HP to match its new maximum HP. You may also wish to update the base creature's name to reflect that it is now a Crew. If the base creature was a spellcaster, and you have given it Joint Summoning, Simultaneous Casting, or United Casting, you will need to update the creature's spellcasting entries according to the instructions for the relevant Crew Ability. These instructions can be found in the abilities' description tab, and follow the heading, \"template\". You may also find taking a look at some of the spellcasters from @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.J5arLCsj7pbrI1eQ]{Crews} a useful example for how each of these three abilities modifies the base creature's spellcasting entries. </p><p><em><strong>Please Note</strong></em><strong> -</strong> While the Crew Template has modified your creature's strikes, current limitations with the NPC sheets for the PF2e system on Foundry mean that the modified values  will not be displayed on the sheet, however the damage adjustment will apply correctly when rolled. </p><h3 class=\"dark\">Step 5. Customization (Optional)</h3><p><strong>Weak and Elite Crews -</strong> If you wish to apply an Elite or Weak template to adjust the strength of your created Crew, that adjustment should be applied now. The way Weak and Elite adjustments are implemented in Foundry VTT the order of application does not matter. You can apply the Weak/Elite adjustment either prior to, or after, applying your Crew Template.</p><p><strong>Crews with Ancestries -</strong> Should you wish to produce a Crew of a particular Ancestry, you may also apply one of the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.QibnMkhhPYrIrwG5]{Ancestry Templates} to your Crew now.</p><p><strong>Additional Crew Abilities - </strong>The Crew templates are designed to increase the power of the base creature to represent the strength of a team of creatures working together. While the number of Crew Abilities granted was selected to provide an adequate bump in power for the increase in level for either version of the template, you may find you wish to create a particularly well-trained or coordinated version of a Crew. In which case, you may wish to add an additional Crew Ability to your new Crew by dragging it from the tables in Step 2. Or, perhaps you wish to create an especially poorly trained Crew. You can accomplish this  by creating a Crew with less Crew Abilities than usual. </p><p><strong>Crews with Descriptive Templates -</strong> The math for Crews has been constructed to scale with the Base Creature's level. If you wish to apply a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.ri8fswkWP7Bimh8l]{Descriptive Templates}, you should apply it first, before applying the Crew template, to ensure the Crew template functions as intended.</p><p><em><strong>Caution</strong></em> - Stacking Crew and Descriptive templates may produce results that are more or less powerful than expected based on the listed level adjustments.</p></div><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Lore Justification</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>Why are Crews, groups of 4 to 6 individuals, affected by magic and other effects as if they are a single creature? While I can certainly provide a number of mechanical and balance reasons, I believe that a satisfying answer needs to make sense within the world.</p><p>The default lore for how Crews work is sympathetic magic. By sympathetic magic what I mean is that there is some effect present that makes any magic cast upon on member of the crew resonate through all members of the Crew. I've got several possible explanations for the underlying cause of this sympathetic magic; feel free to pick your favourite for your world, include different explanations for different Crews, or invent your own.</p><ul><li><strong>Ritual -</strong> The crew has undergone a ritual blending of blood, sharing of tattoos, or similar process which binds them together for good or for ill. This ritual allows the Crew to benefit from spells that would otherwise only affect one of them, though in exchange they are all affected by harmful spells that would target only a single creature.</li><li><strong>Deific Involvement -</strong> One of the deities has a particular love for teamwork, and smiles upon those who sacrifice their individual needs for the good of their fellows. Teams that train together, and act as one when facing their foes, receive this deity's boon, which creates a web of sympathetic magic between the members.</li><li><strong>Empathetic Resonance -</strong> The ties of sympathetic magic are not actually a conduit. Only a single creature might experience an effect, but either due to an empathetic response, or by disrupting the cohesion of the group, the aggregate effect on the group produces a result that matches what we might expect if it were cast on a single creature.</li></ul></div></details><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Usage</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>The Crew Template has been designed so that you can safely substitute any individual creature for a Crew of the same level with minimal impact on the balance of your game. If you are running a campaign where the majority of adversaries are humanoids, you may wish to increase the proportion of crews your party faces as they level up. Doing so will create a clear sense of progression as their opposition is forced to send larger numbers of foes to muster an adequate challenge to your party. This can be particularly effective if you apply the Crew template to foes your players have faced before. </p><p>If you desire, Crews could make up the majority of the opposition in your campaign without any undue impacts on your campaign balance. However, if you do choose to take that approach, you will want to ensure the majority of treasure comes either from bosses or story/achievement rewards. The equipment carried by crews will typically be well below your party's level. </p><p>There is of course no requirement that the Crew Template be applied only to humanoids; any creature that is between size Tiny and Large can be turned into a Crew of creatures using the templates in Step 1. This is especially useful at high levels when you may find that there are fewer premade NPCs available for use with the template. Fey and Outsiders are prime targets to turn into high level crews. </p><p>While Crews were designed to represent groups of your party's weaker foes, if your narrative supports it a Crew can be a satisfying boss encounter. Many of the Crew Abilities give the Crew better action economy, making for more dynamic encounters.</p></div></details><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Design Philosophy</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>Crews materialized as a means to counteract the \"Bandit in Ebony Armour\" issue that is observed in games with level-based scaling like Oblivion or Skyrim. In these games as the players level up the whole world levels up with them, which can undermine any feeling of progression, especially if your party are facing similar foes. Crews are designed to counteract that experience that by allowing you to easily throw a group of lower level adversaries against your players, while still providing a challenge appropriate to their level. By expanding the scale of their combats, it creates a sense of progression. This can be particularly effective if you apple the template to foes the party has faced before. </p><p>The obvious question is:\"Why invent Crews at all, why not simply use troops?\" The answer is multi-faceted, but primarily comes down to maintaining game balance.  If you were to replace a large proportion of the creatures your PCs faced with Paizo's troops, AC becomes largely meaningless and Reflex saves play a disproportionate role in determining the defensive capabilities of the party. Moreover, on the offensive side Troop Defences shift the balance of the game considerably towards the use of low level, repeatable area effect spells as a means to reliably trigger the troops weakness and bypass the damage thresholds, while making many single target spells virtually unusable. Finally, troops are difficult to use in play, their unique mechanics and the sheer number of individual tokens to be moved (should you choose to utilize the troop's capability to spread out) make running them a lot of extra work. Meaning that Troops are best saved for the occasional encounter and are not viable as the bread and butter of your campaign.</p><p>With that in mind Crews have been designed to minimize any changes to the overall balance of the game while still allowing your players to feel as though they are fighting a large group of enemies. To this end a minor weakness to area effect and splash damage has been included to preserve the feeling of area effect magic being especially effective against groups of foes, and crews can be targeted twice for abilities such as swipe allowing your martial character who have specialized into fighting multiple foes to feel effective and in their element when fighting Crews (Note: this is not meant to include cantrips like electric arc which do not need the help, which is why I have worded the ability as effects which require you to select two adjacent creatures, but at your discretion you might choose to allow abilities like ricochet shot, through shot, or even a spell like scorching ray to target the Crew a second time. I recommend erring on the side of caution should you choose to do so, if an ability interpreted as being able to work this way seems too good to be true it probably is). But otherwise the Crew acts exactly like a single creature would, meaning spells and effects that target a single creature function normally for the Crew.  This means that aside from a minor buff to abilities designed to fight groups of enemies, the fundamental balance of the various offensive abilities is preserved. On the defensive side, Crews have standard attacks which mostly target AC, with the occasional creature having spells or abilities that allow it to target saving throws, in line with most other creatures in the bestiaries, this maintains the balance of the various defenses a player might choose from. </p><p>Now Crews needed to be higher level than the base creature otherwise they don't serve the stated goals. I wanted the Crews to be of a reasonable size to fit on most battle maps, and settled on a group of 4 to 6 individuals. With the understanding that working closely together would allow the individuals to stand closer together, meaning they could safely occupy an area roughly equivalent to that taken up by 4 individual creatures of the same size.  One unfortunate side effect of this is that Crew's composed of huge or gargantuan creatures are not feasible due to their size, which is a real shame I love the idea of a Crew of giants. Thinking about 4 squares for medium creature sort of naturally led to considering a level adjustment of +4.  To determine the appropriate amount by which to boost the various abilities and stats for the Crew Template, the Creature Building tables from the Gamemastery Guide were used as a baseline and I looked at the average increase a creature would experience to their checks and DCs when going up 4 levels, and imitated that, with the boost being lower for low level creatures to match the slower progression in values for creatures level 4 and below.</p><p>Now when you're advancing a creature by 4 levels, raw increases to its statistics are insufficient to create a compelling creature, the creature should also have more powerful and intersting abilities. To that end I created the Crew Abilities listed in Step. These abilities were created with a mind towards developing abilities that reinforced the theme of a group of individuals working together to great effect. Like many of the other abilities included in Mercenary Market Volume 1. I've generally tried to err on the side of abilities that are more active in nature, with many of the passive abilities improving the capabilities of existing actions. The most involved of these abilities are those that relate to spellcasting.</p><p>For spellcasters a raw increase in stats is unlikely to create a satisfying or effective opponent, so an alternate means of advancement had to be considered. Three primary abilities that were created to boost the Crew's spellcasting capabilities while reinforcing the theme of a Crew of lower level mages working together, Joint Summoning, Simultaneous Casting and United Casting . Each of these abilities reinforces the Crew's capabilities in a different way. Joint Summoning plays on the fantasy of a group of summoners working together to call forth powerful creatures to do their bidding by providing the Crew with extra slots of high power specifically for summoning spells, of the three abilities it represents a much smaller increase in power, meaning it can be used alongside either united casting or simultaneous casting. United Casting takes the idea of many mages working together to produce greater effects by raising the level of the base creature's spell slots allowing it to upcast any of its existing low level spells. Finally, Simultaneous Casting provides the Crew with more weaker spells and allows it to simultaneously cast a cantrip along with one of its spells each turn, it balances out this power by not granting the Crew any new higher level spell slots meaning its spells will always be below the party's level. Given the large power increase represented by both United Casting and Simultaneous Casting the two cannot be used together on the same Crew. </p><p>The Crew Templates let you quickly create a wide variety of crews from existing NPCs. With the Crew Abilities you can even generate different crews from the same Base Creature by selecting different Crew Abilities, to represent a group made up of the same foes that have undergone different training.  <br /><br />The last sticking point was the lore - how do we justify this group of four to six people being treated by various spells and effects as a single creature. I've included a separate dropdown entry with my lore justifications, so such a critical detail isn't lost in these ramblings.<br /><br />Ultimately I'm quite satisfied with the final result, as it allows for a campaign where your players face down a primarily human opposition without needing to have their opposition continually levelling up with them, instead you can slowly sprinkle more elite fighters and lieutenants in while using crews for the bulks of the opposition's forces. Especially at low levels the existance of the Ragtag Crew, which provides a +2 level adjustment allows for a steady sense of progression. Hopefully you'll find it as satisfying in play as I do.</p></div></details></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"9gfeVJcuMhGzcjlY","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Example Crews","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">Example Crews</h4><hr /><p style=\"width:85%\">In this Demo, example crews for the Archer, Conjuror and Provocateur are available to give you an idea of how the crew template functions.</p><h2 class=\"stylish\" style=\"text-align:center\">Catalogue of NPC Crews</h2><table style=\"width:85%;border-style:hidden;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;color:#050e18\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr class=\"crews\"><td class=\"crews\"><details open style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Archer Crews by level</strong></summary><div style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:1.0em\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.zs7z21iM7dKWRTZw]{Ragtag Archer Crew [3-5]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.epP15SjHtVA1blif]{Archer Crew [5-7]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.LJKxdektZW7R4fbz]{Archer Crew [8-10]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.jdSGnCMNKraqYIiF]{Archer Crew [11-13]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.ZJducXdaopuCsBZY]{Archer Crew [14-16]}</p></div></details></td><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Bandit Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Barrister Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details open style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Conjuror Crews by level</strong></summary><div style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:1.0em\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.7JsdCuwApj7aWBG9]{Conjuror Crew, Ragtag [3-4]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.48lHW9t0fKgHCns8]{Conjuror Crew [5-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.GjzIccQE1gB5U8al]{Conjuror Crew [7-8]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.vB3wzYRuN9l8yRIV]{Conjuror Crew [9-10]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.aZjLU0AS5FAkamZe]{Conjuror Crew [11-12]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.OTuQvpGudSH4Fxg1]{Conjuror Crew [13-14]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.ZSbantD5tiFPVLed]{Conjuror Crew [15-16]}</p></div></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\"><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Cultist Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Cutpurse Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Doctor Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Enforcer Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\"><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Guard Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Guardian Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Hunter Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Hydromancer Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\"><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Mage For Hire Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Monk Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Necromancer Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Ogre Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\"><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Priestess Crews by level</strong></summary><div style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:1.0em\"><p></p></div></details></td><td class=\"crews\"><details open style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Provocateur Crews by level</strong></summary><div style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:1.0em\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.NFHzNYHn9zR8xpsO]{Provocateur Troupe, Ragtag [3-4]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.IkKqzHuP6xfxo8tx]{Provocateur Troupe [5-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.jN3Dj5lbMWyr8V4O]{Provocateur Troupe [7-8]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.aYTgRnmzyaAgDEZX]{Provocateur Troupe [9-10]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.2MItLiBB4U6zuTrH]{Provocateur Troupe [11-12]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.JBtBitMPSWsFKzLC]{Provocateur Troupe [13-14]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.G7oAfCK1t0iRBxb1]{Provocateur Troupe [15-16]}</p></div></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Ravager Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Runic Warrior Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\"><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Sprite Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Tactician Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><details style=\"margin-left:0.5em;font-size:0.8em\"><summary><strong>Wrestler Crews by level</strong></summary></details></td><td class=\"crews\" style=\"background:#e3ddcf\"><strong> </strong></td></tr></tbody></table><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Usage</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>NPCs crews are intended to be direct replacements for individual NPCs of the same level, with minimal impact on balance. Thus, instead of introducing a new NPC mook of 12th level as your players fight their way through an organization, you might instead introduce a Crew made up of 8th level NPCs that the players have fought before. By utilizing Crews in this fashion, it will feel like their foes are forced to throw more enemies at them as they grow in power. More details about the design philosophy of Crews and their usage can be found in the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.9gfeVJcuMhGzcjlY]{Crew Templates} entry. </p><p>The Crews presented above are all pre-modified using the Crew Template, however as is typical for the Crew Template, their equipment has not been adjusted. In a campaign where you are making extensive use of Crews you will want to reward the party with loot from other sources, for example, story rewards or loot from bosses.  While you can add additional copies of each item carried by the Crew to more accurately represent all the arms and armour carried by the crew, doing so results in the party receiving a lot of low level gear that is, in my experience, not worth tracking.</p><p>As is typical for the NPCs presented in Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1, Crews are presented with the bare minimum for gear, based on table 2-4: Safe Items from the Gamemastery Guide, focusing solely on fundamental rune progression. When adapting these Crews for use in your games as adversaries, you may wish to equip your Crews with additional consumables that are narratively appropriate. </p></div></details></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"J5arLCsj7pbrI1eQ","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Descriptive Templates","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">NPCs with Personality</h4><hr /><p style=\"width:85%\">Here you'll find a collection of templates that allow you to modify your NPCs based on a descriptive adjective. A handle of templates have been selected for the Demo, with the remainder being found only in the full version of the module. Each template will give the base creature a unique ability or action that is evocative of the templates' adjective. Many of these templates will also increase or decrease the level of the creature.</p><h2 class=\"stylish\">Instructions</h2><div style=\"width:90%;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:3.5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><h3 class=\"dark\">Step 1. Select Template</h3><p style=\"padding-bottom:0;margin-bottom:0\">Select a Descriptive Template from those listed below that matches the evocative quirk or characteristic you want your NPC to have. The Templates are organized by level adjustment, with +1 templates increasing the level of the creature they are applied to by 1, while -1 templates decrease the level of the creature they are applied to by 1.</p></div><table style=\"width:85.1095%;border-style:hidden;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:41.3379%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;height:19px\"><strong>Level Adjustment</strong></td><td style=\"width:58.8336%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;height:19px\"><strong>Templates</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:50px\"><td style=\"width:41.3379%;text-align:center;color:#050e18;background:#CFC5AF\"><strong>+1</strong></td><td style=\"width:58.8336%;text-align:center;background:#CFC5AF;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-templates.J3mK8pMKdEsJ1xgL]{Bold Template}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Cunning Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Hardy Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Lucky Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Protective Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Sorcerous Template</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:41.3379%;text-align:center;background:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><strong>0</strong></td><td style=\"width:58.8336%;text-align:center;background:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-templates.Mv8TaQXZeg3IfQi9]{Boastful Template}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Brutish Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Cowardly Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Oblivious Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Slight Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Watchful Template</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:41.3379%;text-align:center;color:#050e18;background:#CFC5AF\"><strong>-1</strong></td><td style=\"width:58.8336%;text-align:center;background:#CFC5AF;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Clumsy Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-templates.lCM1lqs9zB1PWHPn]{Foolish Template}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Frail Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Punchable Template</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:41.3379%;text-align:center;color:#050e18;background:#e3ddcf\"><strong>-2</strong></td><td style=\"width:58.8336%;text-align:center;background:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Convalescent Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Feeble Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Inept Template</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Unlucky Template</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:41.3379%;text-align:center;color:#050e18;background:#CFC5AF\"><strong>-3</strong></td><td style=\"width:58.8336%;text-align:center;background:#CFC5AF;color:#050e18\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">Doddering Template</p></td></tr></tbody></table><div style=\"width:90%;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:3.5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><h3 class=\"dark\">Step 2. Apply Template</h3><p>Apply your selected Descriptive Template from Step 1 by dragging it to the NPC token or character sheet, of your choice. After you have dropped it on the token or sheet the Template will automatically apply any appropriate bonuses or penalties and grant any new abilities using the grant item rule element to the NPC. </p><h3 class=\"dark\">Step 3. Manual Adjustments</h3><p>Many of the Descriptive Templates will require small adjustments that could not be automated. If the NPC's maximum HP has increased after the application of the template, you will need to adjust their current HP to match their new maximum. If your base creature has non-strike effects or abilities that deal damage, the damage of these abilities will need to be manually adjusted according to the instructions on each template. This is also an opportune time to review your chosen template for other required manual adjustments. If you have selected one of the level -2 templates you may need to adjust the creature's spellcasting entries. </p><p>Additionally, while you're reviewing your template, take note of any effects listed under the \"effect\" heading on the template, as these will need to be manually adjudicated during play.</p></div><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Usage</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>These templates are designed to allow you to quickly adjust individual creatures to have particular evocative quirks, some of which may be positive and others detrimental. In either case, the creature's level will be adjusted as described in the Level Adjustment column of the table.</p><p>While these templates might create a creature that would typically be considered uncommon or even rare, I recommend that you do not increase the DC to recall knowledge. The strengths and weaknesses of the various templates are key pieces of information to share with your players and have been designed with the expectation that your players will be targeting these weaknesses or attempting to avoid their opposition's strengths. Making that information easier for your players to learn will make for more satisfying and memorable encounters with the modified NPCs, by allowing players to plan around their abilities. </p></div></details><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Design Philosophy</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>The templates were designed to focus on active abilities, and specific strengths or weaknesses the players can defend against or exploit. Most templates are associated with an ability that the creature either, can use, in the case of beneficial abilities, or must use in response to a certain trigger, in the case of detrimental abilities.</p><p>Level Plus templates have been designed to be slightly weaker than an elite creature on average, but will out perform a standard Elite creature, when doing something a creature that could be described with that adjective could reasonably expected to excel at.</p><p>Level +0 templates have been designed to include some positives and negatives and produce creatures that should have roughly the same capabilities as the bae creature, but will be slightly easier to combat for a party that successfully recalls knowledge about these creatures, and slightly harder for those that do not.</p><p>Level Minus templates have been designed to be slightly stronger than a weak creature on average with key detriments and mandatory free actions that the players can exploit to make these creatures easier to handle.</p></div></details></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"ri8fswkWP7Bimh8l","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Generic Spellcasters","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">Generic Spellcasters</h4><hr /><p style=\"width:85%\">The full version of Mercenary Marketplace contains a catalogue of prebuilt NPCs spellcasters presented without spell lists. These NPCs are intended to be used alongside the @Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.dLMmYYevbHCikFnH]{Generate a Random Spell List} macro to quickly create unique casters for your world.</p><p style=\"width:85%\">In volume 1, each spellcasting Tradition is represented by a single NPC which has been built to be usable as a creature from any level between 1 and 20. </p></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"XAdP7FZyWoeMEfRI","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Introduction to Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div style=\"width:100%;margin:0 auto;padding-top:1rem;padding-bottom:1rem\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div style=\"width:100%;margin:0 auto;padding:1% 2.5%\"><div style=\"justify-content:space-between;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap\"><div style=\"flex:1;background-color:#d9d1bf;padding-left:1.5em;padding-right:1.5em;border:10px solid #CFC5AF\"><h2 class=\"plain\">Introduction</h2><hr /><p>Thank you for picking up the Demo of Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1. Within this module you'll find a curated selection of content from Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1. The full version contains 373 new generic NPCs ready to use in your campaigns and 29 templates that will let you customize your existing library of creatures. </p><p>Quick links to help you find all your new content are provided in the directory. For quick access to the directory, save the @Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.X1a1jfoWS4EqGETN]{Toggle MM Demo Directory} macro to your hotbar.</p><p>If you encounter any bugs or other issues, you can report them at the associated <a class=\"href\" href=\"https://github.com/velara/MercenaryMarketplaceVolume1/issues\">GitHub Issues Tracker</a></p><p>I hope you have as much fun using all these new NPCs as I did creating them!</p><h2 class=\"plain\">New NPCs</h2><hr /><p>There are five broad categories of NPCs included in Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.JWFJTzMI86q256tm]{NPCs with Classes} which are designed to be iconic representatives of the various classes from the Core Rulebook.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.m3ez8MLOFi0NWUSH]{NPCs with Jobs} which are designed to excel at performing specific roles in combat.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.XAdP7FZyWoeMEfRI]{Generic Spellcasters} which are fully statted-out NPCs awaiting the addition of your custom, or randomly generated, spell list.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.J5arLCsj7pbrI1eQ]{Crews} which are small groups of foes to challenge your players with. The provided Crews are examples of NPCs that have had the Crew template applied to them.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.LVylAkC1NWnXxLul]{Troops} which are large groups of foes to challenge your players with.</p><p>You can find all the new NPCs included in Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1 one of three ways.</p><ol><li><p style=\"font-weight:normal;color:black\">By browsing the NPC Catalogues listed in the Directory. For ease of browsing, the new NPCs have been curated into five organized catalogues based on type. Each catalogue is sorted by level and class or combat role as appropriate.</p></li><li><p style=\"font-weight:normal;color:black\">Using the Bestiary Browser. You can browse your new NPCs using the Source filter. Additionally, NPCs have been given tags based on either their class or combat role, allowing you to filter by those traits.</p></li><li><p style=\"font-weight:normal;color:black\">Opening the Mercenary Marketplace Vol. 1 NPCs Compendium in your Compendium Packs tab.</p></li></ol><h2 class=\"plain\">New Templates</h2><hr /><p>There are three types of templates included in Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.QibnMkhhPYrIrwG5]{Ancestry Templates} which allow you to quickly apply an ancestry to an existing NPC.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.9gfeVJcuMhGzcjlY]{Crew Templates} which allow you to convert any NPC into a crew of four to six NPCs working in unison.</p><p style=\"padding-left:1em\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.ri8fswkWP7Bimh8l]{Descriptive Templates} which grant an NPC specific thematic advantages or detriments based on a descriptive adjective.</p><p>You can find all your new Templates in one of three ways.</p><ol><li><p style=\"font-weight:normal;color:black\">By browsing the Template Catalogues listed in the Directory. For ease of browsing, the templates have been curated into three organized catalogues by template type.</p></li><li><p style=\"font-weight:normal;color:black\">Using the Compendium Browser. You can browse your new Templates by using the trait filter for the Template trait.</p></li><li><p style=\"font-weight:normal;color:black\">Opening the Mercenary Marketplace Vol. 1 Creature Templates Compendium in your Compendium Packs tab.</p></li></ol><h2 class=\"plain\">Other Content</h2><hr /><p>With the addition of Crews and Templates a couple new traits have been introduced that have some associated rules. These rules have been detailed in the appropriate sections, but for ease of reference have been complied in the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.ysvcY0zFgA6pn1Ak]{New Rules} journal entry.</p><p>This module also includes some new @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.62pBbzbgeMFzOeHD]{Macros}, the first of which generates randomized spell lists based on user input, and is ideal for use with the generic spellcasters. The second can be used to quickly set up the requisite spellcasting entries for the Sorcerous NPC template, which allows you to quickly add a splash of magical power to your NPCs. </p><h2 class=\"plain\">Full Version</h2><hr /><p>If you end up loving the content of the Mercenary Marketplace Demo, then please consider supporting my work by purchasing the <a href=\"https://velara.itch.io/mercenary-marketplace-v1\">full version</a>.</p></div><div style=\"flex:0 0 1em\"><h4> </h4></div><div id=\"directory\" style=\"flex:0 1 16em;background-color:#0d253f;padding-left:1em;padding-right:1em;padding-top:1em;border:10px solid #050e18\"><div style=\"position:sticky;top:5%;width:16em\"><img style=\"border:0;margin-top:-0.3em\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/directory.png\" /><h4 class=\"directory\">NPC Catalogues</h4><hr /><div style=\"margin-left:3em;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.JWFJTzMI86q256tm]{NPCs with Classes}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.m3ez8MLOFi0NWUSH]{NPCs with Jobs}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.XAdP7FZyWoeMEfRI]{Generic Spellcasters}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.J5arLCsj7pbrI1eQ]{Crews}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.LVylAkC1NWnXxLul]{Troops}</p></div><h4 class=\"directory\">Template Catalogues</h4><hr /><div style=\"margin-left:3em;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.QibnMkhhPYrIrwG5]{Ancestry Templates}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.9gfeVJcuMhGzcjlY]{Crew Templates}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.ri8fswkWP7Bimh8l]{Descriptive Templates}</p></div><h4 class=\"directory\">Other Links</h4><hr /><div style=\"margin-left:3em;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.ysvcY0zFgA6pn1Ak]{New Rules}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.62pBbzbgeMFzOeHD]{Macros}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:black\">@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.2h7OGxE2sIBY8h2k]{Credits &amp; License}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\"><a style=\"color:floralwhite\" href=\"https://github.com/velara/MercenaryMarketVolume1/issues\">GitHub Issues Tracker</a></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\"><a style=\"color:floralwhite\" href=\"https://github.com/velara/MercenaryMarketplaceVolume1/releases\">Release Notes</a></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\"><a style=\"color:floralwhite\" href=\"https://www.patreon.com/MercenaryMarketplace\">Patreon</a></p></div></div></div></div><p style=\"color:floralwhite;font-size:0.8em;margin-left:0.5em\">Compatibility with Pathfinder Second Edition requires Pathfinder Second Edition from Paizo Inc. See <a style=\"color:floralwhite\" href=\"http://localhost:30000/paizo.com/pathfinder\">paizo.com/pathfinder</a> to learn more about Pathfinder. Paizo Inc. does not guarantee compatibility, and does not endorse this product.</p></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"gkN2qUJTnou7N3nS","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Macros","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">Macros</h4><hr /><div style=\"margin-left:10%;width:90%\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;margin-left:-5%\">There are eight macros included in Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1. Seven of which are available in the demo.</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.X1a1jfoWS4EqGETN]{Toggle Mercenary Marketplace Vol. 1 Directory Macro}.</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.dLMmYYevbHCikFnH]{Generate a Random Spell List Macro}.<br />@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.GFc0qSPQQb7UrN06]{Arcane Ancestral Cantrip}.<br />@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.6h2oa86ZN4xOPSQq]{Divine Ancestral Cantrip}.<br />@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.t73Cb6tJzvKwd3sI]{Occult Ancestral Cantrip}.<br />@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.g5wjnIPgSqByo7Kq]{Primal Ancestral Cantrips}.<br />@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-macros.A36zBYLenNrDZdc6]{Grant Innate Spells}.</p></div><h2 class=\"stylish\" style=\"margin-top:1.5em\">Toggle Mercenary Marketplace Directory</h2><p style=\"width:90%;margin:0;padding:0;margin-left:5%\">When run, this macro will either:</p><div style=\"width:90%;margin-left:10%\"><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\"><strong>A)</strong> Open the Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1 Directory journal entry.</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\"><strong>B)</strong> If the Directory is already open and not your active window, it will bring it to the front and maximize it.</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\"><strong>C)</strong> If the Directory is your active window it will close it.</p></div><h2 class=\"stylish\" style=\"margin-top:1em\">Generate a Random Spell List - (Limited in Demo)</h2><p style=\"width:90%\">When run, this macro will generate a random list of spells of your chosen tradition based on your specifications. You can limit the rarity of spells it can pull from, select specific schools you'd like to prioritize for inclusion, include heightened versions of spells on the list, and prioritize or ban specific traits.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">The macro will generate a number of spells for each level based on the value you input, with no duplicates. If no spells remain that match your specifications, it will instead pull from an unfiltered list.</p><p>The demo version is limited to generating lists containing only cantrips and level 1 spells.</p><h2 class=\"stylish\">Sorcerous Template Setup - (Full Version Only)</h2><p style=\"width:90%\">When run, this macro will add sorcerous spellcasting to either the NPC character sheet you have open (if it is your active window), or the NPC token you have selected if no NPC character sheet is your currently active window.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">It will add a spontaneous spellcasting entry with 1 spell slot per level, and a focus spellcasting entry with 1 focus point and populate these entries with the granted spells and bloodlines spells for your selected Sorcerous bloodline. The macro will also set the NPC's skill for the skill associated with that bloodline's spellcasting tradition to a value determined by the NPC's level, if that value is higher than the NPC's unmodified skill.</p><h2 class=\"stylish\">Grant Ancestral Cantrips</h2><p style=\"width:90%\">When run, these macro will add an innate spellcasting entry of the appropriate tradition (arcane, divine, occult, or primal) to either the NPC character sheet you have open (if it is your active window), or the NPC token you have selected if no NPC character sheet is your currently active window.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">Each tradition has a separate macro, which will prompt you to select a single cantrip of that tradition, it will then add a innate spellcasting entry of the appropriate tradition and populate the spellcasting entry with your chosen cantrip and set the spell DC and spell attack modifier to appropriate values. <br /></p><p style=\"width:90%\"><strong>Note </strong>if the NPC already has a spellcasting entry you will likely wish to modify the added DC to better reflect their spellcasting proficiency. There is a separate macro for each</p><h2 class=\"stylish\">Grant Innate Spells</h2><p style=\"width:90%\">When run, this macro will add an innate spellcasting entry to either the NPC character sheet you have open (if it is your active window), or the NPC token you have selected if no NPC character sheet is your currently active window.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">The entries tradition and key stat are set by flags on the actor. Similar flags also allow you to specify the spells to be added to this entry. Using these flags it will add an innate spellcasting entry of the appropriate tradition and populate the spellcasting entry with the spell specified in the flags heightened to the specified level and with the specified number of uses.</p><p style=\"width:90%\"></p><p style=\"width:90%\"><strong>Technical Specifications</strong><br />For an example see the rule elements for @Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-abilities.G2DiKLuUrOQ8ifUN]{Elf, Seer}.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">The path to store the flags should you wish to make your own is: flags.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace.grantedSpellcasting.{tradition}. Where {tradition} is replaced with the desired tradition arcane, divine, occult, or primal.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">The key ability modifier is stored at mercenary-marketplace.grantedSpellcasting.{tradition}.keyStat and should be specified using the three letter abbreviation str, dex, con, int, wis, or cha.</p><p style=\"width:90%\">The spell are stored at mercenary-marketplace.grantedSpellcasting.{tradition}.spells. Each spell is added in the following format. [\"Source\", \"Spell Name\", Level, Uses]. Level and Uses can be omitted in which case they will default to the spells base level and 1 respectively. The spell name should be capitalized for example \"Detect Magic\", and the source entry can be set to any string value.</p><p></p></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"62pBbzbgeMFzOeHD","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"New Rules","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">New Rules - Quick Reference</h4><hr /><h2 class=\"stylish\">Crew Trait</h2><p style=\"width:90%\">The Crew trait indicates that a creature is actually a collection of 4 to 6 trained individuals working together in unison. Any creature with the Crew trait is treated as a single creature for the purposes of spells and effects. However, it may be selected twice for abilities that require you to select two adjacent creatures, such as swipe.</p><h2 class=\"stylish\">Mandatory Trait</h2><p style=\"width:90%\">The Mandatory trait is only ever applied to abilities with a trigger. If the trigger occurs for an ability with the Mandatory trait a creature with that ability must use it, even if it is to the creature's detriment.</p></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"ysvcY0zFgA6pn1Ak","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"NPCs with Classes","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">NPCs with Class</h4><hr /><p style=\"width:92%\">In this Demo only the Cleric, Fighter, Rogue and Wizard are available. All other detail dropdowns are empty.</p><p style=\"width:92%\">Here you'll find a catalogue of NPCs built to resemble members of one of the twelve classes from the Core Rulebook.  In Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1, each class is represented by a single NPC, with multiple scaled iterations allowing for NPCs from level  1 and 18. </p><h2 class=\"plain\">Catalogue of NPCs by Class</h2><hr /><table style=\"margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;width:92%;border-style:hidden\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;height:19px;font-size:0.9em\"><strong>Alchemist</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;height:19px;font-size:0.9em\"><strong>Barbarian</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;height:19px;font-size:0.9em\"><strong>Bard</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px;vertical-align:top\"><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Alchemists by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Barbarians by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Bards by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Champion</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Cleric</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Druid</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px;vertical-align:top\"><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Champions by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Clerics by level</strong></summary><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.uRLvqoIAtjGzWCFZ]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [1-2]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.XV93IR6dQqdhJ9To]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [3-4]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.GucfeJ75iqQQGqCa]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [5-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.JS3iVWBmEJ9hcl7m]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [7-8]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.vvbH0YtUmqWPlELs]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [9-10]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.N7Dg9H5qQzYgn4PO]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [11-12]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.ajgMdZpsbHSuPRfT]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [13-14]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.6VUxvixmcqOFgFUe]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [15-16]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.tnNUGJ9PD6BmtRdO]{Mercenary Cleric of Travel [17-18]}</p></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Druids by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Fighter</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Monk</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Ranger</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px;vertical-align:top\"><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Fighters by level</strong></summary><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.gEP3r7Idh2pxEZdc]{Mercenary Fighter [1-3]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.20jaZjNJ5jMGntNf]{Mercenary Fighter [4-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.MXs60Y75oSTE0z56]{Mercenary Fighter [7-9]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.hctTM0VU9jOX1ek4]{Mercenary Fighter [10-12]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.VKm7k5if12mVLYv5]{Mercenary Fighter [13-15]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.meHZBMGNlgw3Gbz5]{Mercenary Fighter [16-18]}</p></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Monks by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Rangers by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Rogue</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Sorcerer</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Wizard</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px;vertical-align:top\"><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Rogues by level</strong></summary><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.tJa8LcWzbJxYcDst]{Mercenary Rogue [1-3]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.QkC0uFzNYGqS97mM]{Mercenary Rogue [4-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.JHUiDYDunNrR6fQZ]{Mercenary Rogue [7-9]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.H9bUMe2wOA08wIok]{Mercenary Rogue [10-12]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.521euvbF9z0ChdGI]{Mercenary Rogue [13-15]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.0FUWn1DRgjBuiDHQ]{Mercenary Rogue [16-18]}</p></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Sorcerers by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Wizards by level</strong></summary><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.39WcoXLAVE19JUEa]{Mercenary Wizard [1-2]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.NwJxTzZb7XwmbGRF]{Mercenary Wizard [3-4]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.WkED36XGaWaLVB8s]{Mercenary Wizard [5-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.uRBF4jYThQUI6YN7]{Mercenary Wizard [7-8]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.Ela24uWRAQKJirxm]{Mercenary Wizard [9-10]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.gZhtAmEnlqLC7U8l]{Mercenary Wizard [11-12]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.5AvTCzq7towZNe61]{Mercenary Wizard [13-14]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.iS0JaR9u47qsFKL3]{Mercenary Wizard [15-16]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.R4kFk0cHffbdGhbw]{Mercenary Wizard [17-18]}</p></details></td></tr></tbody></table><div style=\"width:94%;margin:0 auto\"><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Usage</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>NPCs with class have been provided for use for levels between 1 and 18, allowing you to use them with minimal modification for the majority of any campaign.</p><p>Melee characters are listed with a range of three levels, for example [1-3]. The NPC is of the median level; however by applying either the Elite or Weak template, you can use those NPCs for the higher or lower level listed in the range. </p><p>Spellcasting characters are listed with a range of two levels, for example [1-2]. You'll find the actual NPC is the higher of the two levels. Given the increase in power and versatility that comes with learning a new level of spells, it is recommended that you do not use these NPCs with the Elite template, but they are readily compatible with the Weak template. Furthermore, given the adjustments applied by the Weak template to spell damage, I do not recommend adjusting the number of spell slots.</p><p>NPCs have been provided with a minimal amount of gear based on table 2-4: Safe Items from the Gamemastery Guide, focusing entirely on fundamental rune progression. While this means you can slot them into your game with a minimal impact on your party's treasure, if you are using them as the base for a significant foe you will want to expand upon and upgrade upon the gear provided, particularly in terms of consumables, worn or held magic items, and things like scrolls, staves and wands for spellcasting NPCs. Please note however, the NPC statistics already reflect appropriate values for creatures of their level, based on Paizo's creature creation guidelines, so if you are upgrading the fundamental runes (+x potency runes, resilience, striking) I would recommend exercising caution with changing those values, although applying the effects of property runes should be acceptable, especially if your players are level 5+. </p><p>These NPCs are designed to be most appropriate for use as named antagonists,  either directly unmodified or tweaked to match your needs. While NPCs with Class can be dropped into the world to represent generic antagonists of the appropriate player class, care should be taken to avoid the Skyrim bandit problem, where all the background NPCs level up with the party. If you are looking to challenge a high level party with generic underlings, either @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.J5arLCsj7pbrI1eQ]{Crews} or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.LVylAkC1NWnXxLul]{Troops} may be more suitable while maintaining a stronger sense of progression. </p></div></details><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Design Philosophy</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>These NPCs have been designed to emulate player classes, although in many cases abilities have been simplified, condensed or reflavoured to make the NPCs easier to run for GMs. To appropriately capture the flavour of their respective classes, these NPCs with Class tend to have more abilities, than the other NPCs included in Mercenary Market Volume 1, making them more complex to run. These design choices make NPCs with class most appropriate for use as named antagonists. Although, these NPCs will still tend to have fewer  abilities than a PC of the same level, and no attempt has been made to include skill feats or ancestry feats, instead trading that versatility for the slight increase in raw power that is intrinsic to Paizo's creature building guidelines.</p><p>While we have attempted to capture the essence and flavour of each class, we have not restricted ourselves to the abilities and feats described in the core rulebook, some custom abilities have been created. While these new abilities have not been written up as player facing feats, they could be adapted for uncommon or rare player options. Although, if adapted without any tweaking, they will tend to be slightly more powerful than standard player options of the same level, as NPCs tend have fewer, slightly more powerful abilities, to make up for their lack of versatility and to make them easier to run.</p><p>Generally an attempt has been made to remove or modify abilities that are likely to be frustrating for players. For example, many classes get abilities to upgrade successes on saves to critical successes for their highest save, which given the relatively high saves of NPCs can be very frustrating for spellcasting PCs. To counteract this, we have omitted many of these abilities, except in cases were we felt these abilities were essential to the flavour of the class, such as Evasion on the Rogue.</p><p>The progression of these characters is modelled after that of their respective classes, with slight deviations as appropriate.</p></div></details></div></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"JWFJTzMI86q256tm","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"NPCs with Jobs","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">NPCs with Jobs</h4><hr /><p style=\"width:85%\">Here you'll find a catalogue of NPCs built to fill a particular combat role or job.  In volume 1, each role is represented by several NPCs. Multiple versions of different levels exist for each NPC. </p><p style=\"width:85%\">In this demo only the Doctor, Guardian and Necromancer are available, all the other detail dropdowns are empty.</p><h2 class=\"plain\">Catalogue of NPCs by Combat Role</h2><hr /><table style=\"margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;width:90%;border-style:hidden\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Artillery</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Bruiser</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Defender</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px;vertical-align:top\"><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Archers by level</strong></summary></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Hydromancers by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Enforcers by level</strong></summary></details><details style=\"