ls></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Doctors by level</strong></summary><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.vK7mfMwQxtEx9P65]{Doctor [1-3]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.f9AGp30o7RJ9yB2I]{Doctor [4-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.VLbdDtELpaovYUmw]{Doctor [7-9]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.cRLtEbs4aQIYVn7m]{Doctor [10-12]}</p></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Priestesses by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Skirmisher</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Good against Single-Targets</strong></td><td style=\"width:33%;text-align:center;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Good Against Multiple-Targets</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px;vertical-align:top\"><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Cutpurses by level</strong></summary></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Doctors by level</strong></summary><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.vK7mfMwQxtEx9P65]{Doctor [1-3]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.f9AGp30o7RJ9yB2I]{Doctor [4-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.VLbdDtELpaovYUmw]{Doctor [7-9]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.cRLtEbs4aQIYVn7m]{Doctor [10-12]}</p></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Runic Warriors by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Archers by level</strong></summary></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Cutpurses by level</strong></summary></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Doctors by level</strong></summary><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.vK7mfMwQxtEx9P65]{Doctor [1-3]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.f9AGp30o7RJ9yB2I]{Doctor [4-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.VLbdDtELpaovYUmw]{Doctor [7-9]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.cRLtEbs4aQIYVn7m]{Doctor [10-12]}</p></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Enforcers by level</strong></summary></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Provocateurs by level</strong></summary></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Runic Warriors by level</strong></summary></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Wrestlers by level</strong></summary></details></td><td style=\"height:19px;font-size:0.8em;color:#050e18\"><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Conjurors by level</strong></summary></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Guardians by level</strong></summary><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.lpnw05ash7Ta0u6T]{Guardian [1-3]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.mLBjsTBo94iK8GXP]{Guardian [4-6]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.LYFqsURmfnpHXzMA]{Guardian [7-9]}</p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.sH9NvA3CQAxBaIMp]{Guardian [10-12]}</p></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Hydromancers by level</strong></summary></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Priestesses by level</strong></summary></details><details style=\"text-align:left;margin-left:15%\"><summary><strong>Ravagers by level</strong></summary></details></td></tr></tbody></table><div style=\"width:92%;margin:0 auto\"><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Usage</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>Some NPCs can fill multiple roles and will appear on the table in several locations. </p><p>Melee characters are listed with a range of three levels, for example [1-3]. The NPC is of the median level; however by applying either the Elite or Weak template, you can use those NPCs for the higher or lower level listed in the range. </p><p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em)\">Spellcasting characters are listed with a range of two levels, for example [1-2]. You'll find the actual NPC is the higher of the two levels. Given the increase in power and versatility that comes with learning a new level of spells, it is recommended that you do not use these NPCs with the Elite template, but they are readily compatible with the Weak template. Furthermore, given the adjustments applied by the Weak template to spell damage, I do not recommend adjusting the number of spell slots.</p><p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em)\">NPCs have been provided with a minimal amount of gear based on table 2-4: Safe Items from the Gamemastery Guide, focusing entirely on fundamental rune progression. While this means you can slot them into your game with a minimal impact on your party's treasure, if you are using them as the base for a significant foe you will want to expand upon or upgrade upon the gear provided, particularly in terms of consumables, worn or held magic items, and things like scrolls, staves and wands for spellcasting NPCs. The NPC statistics already reflect appropriate values for creatures of their level based on Paizo's creature creation guidelines, so if you are upgrading the fundamental rules (+x potency rules, resilience, striking) I would recommend exercising caution with changing those values, although applying the effects of property runes should be acceptable, especially if your players are level 5+. </p><p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em)\">These NPCs are designed to have lower complexity than the NPCs with Classes and are particularly appropriate for use as supporting characters. For major named antagonists it may be beneficial to select one to two feats from an appropriate class, ancestry or skill to expand upon their versatility and make for a more complex villain. </p><p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em)\">For higher level threats, the intention is that individual NPCs of this sort stop being a threat to the party, and you need to transition to using @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-journals.1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX.JournalEntryPage.J5arLCsj7pbrI1eQ]{Crews}. I've intentionally not created any NPCs with jobs over level 12 to explicitly encourage this transition.</p></div></details><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Design Philosophy</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>In making these NPCs I have split them into seven different combat roles. Each NPC was designed to fulfill one or more of these combat roles, while remaining true to the core identity of whatever job that NPC has. Thus, abilities have been designed such that the Tactician has abilities that feel appropriate for someone who makes their living as a tactician, while the Necromancer has abilities that feel appropriate for someone who raises the dead, even through both act as leaders. In comparison to the NPCs with Class, NPCs with Jobs have been generally designed to have fewer and simpler abilities to make them easier to run; and while these NPCs can make for great named antagonists they tend to be simpler in design making them especially suitable for use as lackeys.</p><p>Many of these NPCs have brand new abilities that are particularly suited to their theme, these abilities will tend to be more powerful than a player's ability of the same level to compensate for the relative lack of breadth these NPCs have compared to player characters. However, with some tweaking, an ambitious GM could turn these unique mechanics and the progression demonstrated between the lower and high level NPCs with jobs into player facing archetypes. In general, many of these abilities are intended to be player visible. What I mean by that is, they should be discoverable with recall knowledge, and that the abilities have been designed to be things the NPCs actively do, rather than passive bonuses. Where passive bonuses do exist I've endeavored to make them significant enough and obvious enough based on the concept that I hope your players will be able to guess to avoid a particular tactic or save based on what sort of NPC they are facing. </p><p>I've only included NPCs with levels between 1 to 12 in this collection, with the notion that based on what Paizo has created, level 1 to 12 is a believable level of power for these more generic NPCs, and they could be feasible slotted into your adventure paths and Golarion games without breaking versamillatude. As your party moves into the mid to high levels individual NPCs give way to crews of NPCs to appropriately challenge your players, while creating a sense of realistic scaling in the scope and stakes of what your PCs are able to accomplish. With the Crew Templates these foes can thus remains viable threats up until the final few levels of your campaigns.</p></div></details></div></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"m3ez8MLOFi0NWUSH","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":1250000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Troops","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"mmDemo-logo\"><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo/art/MM.png\" /></div><div class=\"main-box\"><h4 class=\"mimic-h1\">Troops</h4><hr /><p style=\"width:85%\">Here you'll find a catalogue of all the new troops included in Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1. In volume 1, troops have been produced for levels between 4 and 18. The demo contains 4 troops for you to use.</p><h2 class=\"plain\">Catalogue of Troops by Level</h2><hr /><table style=\"width:85%;border-style:hidden;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Level</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;background-color:#050e18;font-size:0.9em;height:19px\"><strong>Troops</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\"><strong>4</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.UgGzOfg3Sb53c4yX]{Goblin Raiders [4]}, Unenthusiastic Militia</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><strong>5</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\">Angry Mob, @Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.LH3TX2hHy71ce2Mm]{Beleaguered Mercenary Company [5]}</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\"><strong>6</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\">Hunting Party, Spear Infantry</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><strong>7</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\">Archer Battalion, Cavalry Cohort</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\"><strong>8</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\">Armoured Infantry, Untested Warmage Circle</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><strong>9</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\">Drake Slayers, Druidic Circle</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\"><strong>10</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\">Fervent Faithful, Northern Raiding Party</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><strong>11</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\">Bloodthirsty Mob, Hardened Spear Infantry</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\"><strong>12</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\">Mercenary Company, Sappers</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><strong>13</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\">Decorated Archer Battalion, Demonic Cultists</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\"><strong>14</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\">Decorated Cavalry Cohort, @Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.sRTSD4oxm20EBWnd]{Royal Guard [14]}</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><strong>15</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\">@Compendium[pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo.mmDemo-actors.T54v9SD1BNCmcHKx]{Mad Mutagenists [15]}</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\"><strong>16</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\">Thane's Raiding Party</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\"><strong>17</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#e3ddcf;color:#050e18\">Enlightened Disciples</td></tr><tr style=\"height:19px\"><td style=\"width:12.5504%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\"><strong>18</strong></td><td style=\"width:87.4067%;height:19px;font-size:0.8em;background-color:#cfc5af;color:#050e18\">Imperial Crown Guard</td></tr></tbody></table><div style=\"width:90%;margin:0 auto\"><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Usage</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>Given the limitations of FoundryVTT at present, templates like Weak and Elite do not affect inline damage rolls. Given that inline rolls are the primary sort of damage roll used for troops, each troop is presented at a single level only rather than a level range. I don't recommend trying to modify your troops with the Weak and Elite adjustments unless you're prepared to make a number of manual adjustments.</p><p>Troops have been presented as Gargantuan creatures to reflect the rules, however, if you wish to have troops that can alter their shape per the rules in Form Up, you will wish to adjust the size to medium and place 16 medium tokens all linked to the initial imported actor. This set up allows you to freely move the individual members around while still providing a single shared health bar. If you not wish to take this approach and would instead prefer to treat the troop as a gargantuan creature, then you will likely want to treat the troops level as one level lower, especially in the case of troops that predominately deal melee damage. The inability to alter the shape of the troop will have a strongly detrimental impact of the troop's damage output, as it will be unable to shift around to catch most of the party with its attacks. For troops that mostly rely on ranged damage or spellcasting, this adjustment is unnecessary. </p></div></details><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Troop Creation Guidelines</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>The Full version of Mercenary Marketplace contains guidelines for creating your own troops.</p></div></details><details><summary class=\"exposition\"><h2 class=\"stylish-summary\">Design Philosophy</h2></summary><div style=\"width:90%;background-color:floralwhite;padding:10px 30px;margin-left:5%;margin-top:0px;border-radius:0px 0px 15px 15px\"><p>I find the weakness of Paizo's troops to Area Effect spells to be very unsatisfying, the weakness has the same effect whether you spend a first level burning hands spell or a 10th level meteor swarm. Whereas I feel that a higher level area effect spell used on a troop should produce a proportionately greater effect. My solution to address this grip was is to replace the weakness with a Area Effect Vulnerability, which decreases the degree of success for troops against area effect spells, thus making their effectiveness naturally scale with the power of the spell. If you find you'd prefer the standard troop weaknesses, remove the Troop Area Effect Vulnerability and give the troop a weakness with a value equal to double its listed weakness to splash damage.</p><p>Wherever possible I've chosen to create abilities for these troops that reflect the fantasy evoked by the troop's name. Though, like all other actors included in Mercenary Marketplace Volume 1, I have not provided an explicit lore entry, as they are intended to be adapted to your world.</p></div></details></div></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"LVylAkC1NWnXxLul","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"name":"Mercenary Marketplace Demo Journals","ownership":{"default":0,"bfgnTwSJe6w6fxpV":3},"flags":{"pf2e-mercenary-marketplace-demo":{"ismmDemo":true},"core":{"viewMode":1,"sourceId":"JournalEntry.8DcD4RyopUR4Zagd"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.6.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1662562755593,"modifiedTime":1673975683384,"lastModifiedBy":"bfgnTwSJe6w6fxpV"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"1s34nyLF4vYUxsHX"}
